objects.description:
Barkitecture is a custom doghouse design show, contest, silent auction and, most importantly, fundraiser! From its inception in 2005, Barkitecture has become an Austin favorite and gained national exposure. Hosted by Animal Lovers of Austin, Inc. (a 501(c)3 organization) this architectural dog-centric event showcases doghouses created by Austin’s best and
brightest architects, interior designers and builders. A fair that’s fun for all ages drawing in pooches and people alike, Barkitecture attendees and their dogs get to check
out and bid on these one-of-a-kind doghouses, learn about adoption opportunities from Austin Pets Alive!, shop local vendor booths, enjoy a Fashound Show, hit the
photo booth with your pooch and check out face painting for the kiddos! This year we are delighted to be partnering with Austin Pets Alive! as our sole beneficiary for funds raised and are excited to hold the event in the heart of SOCO, thanks to Jo’s Coffee and Hotel San Jose. The event is FREE to enjoy
objects.name: Barkitecture Austin 2016 - Free EVENT

objects.description:
The 30th annual AIA Austin Homes Tour highlights 12 homes that all show the value of using an architect. Showcasing design excellence, quality craftsmanship, and innovative use of materials, each project demonstrates the relationship between the owner and the architect and the results of their collaborative process.

This year's tour features the incredible work of Burton Baldridge Architects, Faye and Walker Architecture, Furman + Keil Architects, Lake|Flato Architects, McKinney York Architects, Mell Lawrence Architects, Nick Deaver Architect, Rauser Design, Rick & Cindy Black Architects, Tom Hurt Architecture, Tornbjerg Design, LLC, and Webber + Studio, Architects.

*Tickets will go on sale September 15th and will be available to purchase online, and at AIA Austin, Nannie Inez, NEST Modern, and Zinger Hardware. $35 in advance; $40 day of the Tour at the four listed locations only.
objects.name: AIA Austin Homes Tour 2016

objects.description:
Come one, come all! The 11th annual Carnival O’ Pizza is back for an afternoon of pizza-themed fun that’s bigger and better than before! 

A celebration of Home Slice’s love for all things pizza, this year’s carnival will take place on Saturday, September 24 from noon to 7 p.m. at the iconic South Congress location. Our free family-friendly event will have over-the-top pizza-themed activities and exciting prizes, with all proceeds to benefit this year's non-profit recipient: Austin Bat Cave! 

Join in on the fun with carnival-inspired games, dancing, a photo booth and raffles to win one of 60 prizes, including a YETI Die Hard Pack, two Sound on Sound Fest Festival passes, and even the chance for one lucky raffle winner to be the only person in the world who can make a reservation at Home Slice for the next year! 

The 2016 Carnival-O-Pizza promises fun for all ages with:

- Kid themed games and booths, including our own invention: Pee Wee Pizzaioli

- Size and speed dough throwing cont
objects.name: Home Slice Carnival O Pizza 2016

Organized by Texas Craft Brewers Guild
